@Renargen14 2012-04-15 13:22 CET: 
One should block tropico4.exe from accessing the internet, following this guide: http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/cc947786%28v=ws.10%29.aspx
The guide you posted is the wrong guide, it is meant for blocking a certain TCP or UDP port. For blocking a specific application only, it is much easier to use the guide I link to above.

@Riael_Krane 2012-04-14 10:29 CET: 
It is not impossible. I've installed this addon over the 1.00 FLT release, and I do have access to all the new buildings in the campaign mode. So, the game does work to some extent. However, as I've posted previously, the game crashes when you finish building a space program building. As soon as you finish building a space program building, a special mini-mission is supposed to load, as is written in the game's manual. However, instead of loading this mission, the game crashes. Since building a space program is a required objective, it is impossible to finish the campaign mode.

Since I've seen no reports of this happening on legally acquired versions of the game, the crash is presumably caused by the crack by Reloaded. Therefore, this release is ***NUKED***.
